9 An Act relating to agricultural fairs and
expositions; amending 2 O.S. 2021, Section 15-24,
10 which relates to items to be considered in
expenditure of funds; modifying language; permitting
11 consideration of certain communications and
supporting equipment; amending 2 O.S. 2021, Section
12 15-55, which relates to election of officers and
directors of the county fair association; requiring
13 voting window; providing procedures for removal of
officers and directors; amending 2 O.S. 2021, Section
14 15-58, which relates to items to be considered in
expenditure of funds; modifying language; permitting
15 consideration of certain communications and
supporting equipment; amending 2 O.S. 2021, Section
16 15-70, which relates to annual levy in support and
maintenance of fair; permitting use of funds for
17 certain communications and supporting equipment; and
providing an effective date.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 15-24, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 Section 15-24. A. The executive board shall:
24 1. Make an estimate of the cost of the free district fair;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1547 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 2. Apportion to each of the counties comprising the association
2 the portion to be borne by each member county together with the plan
3 and items of expenditures; and
4 3. Certify the estimate to the county excise board in each of
5 the member counties in time to be acted on by the county excise
6 board at its annual meeting for making tax levies.
7 B. The items to be considered in the expenditure of funds shall
8 be for:
9 1. Premiums on livestock, poultry, fruit, agriculture,
10 horticultural and dairy products; boys' and girls' club work, school
11 exhibits, culinary products, textile products, needlework and
12 sewing, hand painting, decorating and drawing, and cultivated plants
13 and flowers;
14 2. The necessary expenses of management of free district fairs
15 organized under the provisions of this article, including office
16 expense, postage, telegraph and telephone, digital and electronic
17 communication, Internet and supporting equipment, traveling expenses
18 of secretary within the district in which the fair is held, printing
19 (except premium lists) and necessary office supplies, premium
20 ribbons and badges, clerical help, guards, superintendents and
21 judges; and
22 3. Advertising the fair and for decorating and cleaning the
23 grounds and buildings, and for caring for the grounds during the
24 fair.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1547 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 15-55, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 15-55. A. As soon as practicable, prior to July first,
4 after the election of members of the county fair association, the
5 members elect shall meet at the county seat and shall perfect an
6 organization by the election of a president, vice president,
7 secretary and a board of directors. The members elect shall
8 designate a day where they shall have a twelve-hour window to vote
9 for the election of a president, vice president, secretary, and
10 board of directors. The Board of Directors shall consist of the
11 president, vice president, secretary and four members, and such
12 committees and officers as shall be deemed necessary. The secretary
13 may be selected outside of the association, but must be a resident
14 of the county seat or the town or city where the county fair is
15 held.
16 B. The president, vice president, secretary, or any member of
17 the board of directors may be removed from their position for
18 failure to attend at least fifty percent (50%) of meetings in a
19 calendar year. The president, vice president, secretary, and
20 members of the board of directors may be removed from their
21 positions by a unanimous vote of all other members.
22 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 15-58, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
