(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 Section 15-58. A. The executive board, with such committee as
2 may be selected from the county fair association, shall make an
3 estimate of the cost of the township and county fairs, and shall
4 certify such estimate to the county excise board in time to be acted
5 upon by the county excise board at its annual meeting for making tax
6 levies.
7 B. The items to be considered in the expenditure of funds shall
8 be for:
9 1. Premiums on livestock, poultry, agricultural and
10 horticultural products, dairy products, boys' and girls' club work,
11 products of domestic science and domestic arts, school exhibits,
12 hand painting, decorating and drawing, manufactured articles,
13 cultivated plants and flowers;
14 2. Necessary expenses of management of township and county
15 fairs organized under the provisions of this article, including
16 office expenses, postage, telegraph and telephone, digital and
17 electronic communication, Internet and supporting equipment, salary
18 and traveling expenses of the secretary, printing and necessary
19 office supplies, premium ribbons and badges, clerical help, guards,
20 superintendents and judges;
21 3. Advertising the fairs and for decorating and cleaning the
22 grounds and buildings, and for caring for the grounds and buildings;
23 and
