(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 4. Transportation and arrangement of township fair exhibits at
2 the county fair and county fair exhibits at the Oklahoma State Fair
3 and other State Fairs.
4 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 15-70, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 15-70. A. The county commissioners, the county excise
7 board and all other proper officers of the county may make an annual
8 levy upon all taxable property in the county in an amount not to
9 exceed one-half (1/2) of one (1) mill per annum in counties of more
10 than fifteen thousand (15,000) population. In counties of less than
11 fifteen thousand (15,000) population, the proper officers of the
12 county may make an annual levy upon all taxable property in the
13 county of not exceeding one (1) mill per annum. The purpose of the
14 levy is to raise funds for:
15 1. The support and maintenance of the fair, including the
16 payment of premiums on livestock, poultry, agricultural and
17 horticultural products, dairy products, boys' and girls' club work
18 or other junior agricultural organizations which shall be in one
19 class, products of domestic science and domestic arts, farm women's
20 clubs, hand paintings, cultivated plants and flowers;
21 2. Necessary expenses of management of said fair, including
22 office expenses, postage, telegraph and telephone, digital and
23 electronic communication, Internet and supporting equipment, salary
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1547 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 and traveling expenses of the secretary, printing and necessary
2 office supplies;
3 3. Premium ribbons and badges, clerical help, guards,
4 superintendents and judges;
5 4. Advertising, decorating and cleaning the grounds and
6 buildings; and
7 5. The repair of or erecting buildings owned and controlled by
8 said county that are or will be used for free fair purposes.
9 B. In the counties of this state having a population in excess
10 of fifty-five thousand (55,000), according to the 1940 Federal
11 Decennial Census and in which county there is not authorized a state
12 fair, it shall be the mandatory duty of the county commissioners and
13 the excise board and other officers of the county, to make annual
14 levy for the purposes specified by this section upon all taxable
15 property in such county of not less than one-fourth (1/4) of one (1)
16 mill per annum.
17 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
